'''Claudius Colas''', also known as '''Profesoro V. Esperema''', was a [[France|French]] [[Esperanto|Esperantist]] who lived from 1884 to 1914.<ref name="Esperanto Wikipedia">[[:eo:Claudius Colas|Esperanto Wikipedia]]</ref>  In 1910, he created the [[constructed language]] [[Adjuvilo]], which was a complete language that was never meant to be spoken but instead an effort to help create dissent in the then-growing [[Ido (language)|Ido]] movement.  In 1910, he co-founded [[International Union of Catholic Esperantists|IKUE]], the foremost organization of [[Roman Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[Esperantist]]s in the world. <ref name="Esperanto Wikipedia"/>  He died during the early days of [[World War I]]. <ref>[http://www.bowks.net/worldlang/aux/p_ClaudiusColas.html Auxilingua Project] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071030124712/http://www.bowks.net/worldlang/aux/p_ClaudiusColas.html |date=2007-10-30 }}</ref>

