{{Infobox language |name=Duoni |nativename= |states=[[China]] |region=[[Yunnan]] |ethnicity=[[Hani people|Hani]] |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern]] |fam6=[[Hani languages|Hani]] |fam7=[[Honi language|Hao-Bai]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Duoni''' ({{zh|多尼}}) is a [[Hanoish languages|Southern]] [[Loloish language]] of [[Yunnan]], China. Duoni is spoken in [[Jinping Miao, Yao, and Dai Autonomous County]] and [[Yuanyang County, Yunnan]].
==Distribution== In [[Yuanyang County, Yunnan|Yuanyang County]], the Duoni people are found in the townships of Niujiaozhai 牛角寨 and Zha'e 扎俄.<ref>云南省编辑委员会编. 2009. "元阳县哈尼族情况琐记." In 哈尼族社会历史调查, p.80-83. 民族出版社. {{ISBN|9787105087754}}</ref> In [[Jinping Miao, Yao, and Dai Autonomous County|Jinping County]], Duoni are located in Laojizhai Township 老集寨乡 (in the village clusters 行政村 of Masasi 马撒斯,<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189079</ref> Bailezhai 白乐寨,<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189083</ref> and Dazhupeng 大竹棚<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vIndex.aspx?departmentid=189080</ref>), comprising 793 households and 3,329 persons as of 2005.<ref>金平苗族瑶族傣族自治县民族志1979-2010. 金平苗族瑶族傣族自治県民族宗教事務局編. 雲南民族出版社. 2013年8月. {{ISBN|9787536757028}}</ref>
